# Robot Stack

## Repository Purpose

This repository provides a Python CLI-ish interactive (and someday autonomous) toolset to evaluate, tag, and trigger builds across multiple repositories that make up the Opentrons robot software stack. These tools help analyze changes across repositories, gather and present the information needed to decide which commits need tagging in each repository, and generate a report for each build.

- **Flex robots** using `oe-core`, `ot3-firmware`, and `opentrons`
- **OT-2 robots** using `opentrons-ot2` and `buildroot`
- **Release infrastructure** reference repo: `robot-stack-infra`

The system supports internal and external release channels. This tool helps enforce consistency and correctness before triggering final operating system builds.

## Release Paths

`automation/go.py` supports two release paths. **Flex is the default.**

| Path | Repos synced | App repo (tagging) | Version scheme |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Flex** | `opentrons`, `oe-core`, `ot3-firmware` | `opentrons` | Per-repo prefixes (see Flex semver below) |
| **OT-2** | `opentrons-ot2`, `buildroot` | `opentrons-ot2` | Calendar semver for app + internal; buildroot external uses independent `vX.Y.Z` (see below) |

`robot-stack-infra` is always cloned and pulled for both paths as a reference repo, but is not included in release tables or tagging.

Release branches default by path and channel, but **`just go` accepts overrides** (see Agentic CLI reference). Flex **external** prefers `chore_release-<version>` when that branch exists on the remote. Flex **internal** and OT-2 default to each repo's default branch (`edge` / `main` / `opentrons-develop`). Use `--app-branch` and `--stack-branch REPO=BRANCH` when a release flavor ships from a named branch (for example `chore_release-10.0.0-beta` on `opentrons` while stack repos stay on `main`).

When the release branch differs from the repo default, `just go` prints `git checkout <branch>` before suggested `git tag -a` commands.

## Local Cloned Repos (Source of Truth)

`automation/go.py` (via `just go`) clones and pulls stack repos into the workspace root. When investigating behavior in those projects (version tags, electron-updater, buildroot `write_version.py`, CI actions, release scripts, etc.), **read and search the source in these directories first**. Do not answer from memory or GitHub API alone when a local tree is available.

| Directory | Upstream repo | Release path |
|---|---|---|
| `opentrons/` | Opentrons/opentrons | Flex |
| `oe-core/` | Opentrons/oe-core | Flex |
| `ot3-firmware/` | Opentrons/ot3-firmware | Flex |
| `opentrons-ot2/` | Opentrons/opentrons-ot2 | OT-2 |
| `buildroot/` | Opentrons/buildroot | OT-2 |
| `robot-stack-infra/` | Opentrons/robot-stack-infra | reference only |

- If a directory is missing or only has `.git` metadata, run `uv run just go` (or clone the repo into the path above) before deep investigation.
- Prefer `Grep`, `SemanticSearch`, and `Read` on these paths over `gh api` / remote fetches for implementation details.
- `automation/` in this repo orchestrates releases; stack behavior lives in the cloned repos.

### OT-2 calendar semver

OT-2 uses semver format for electron-updater. **Internal and external channels use different patch schemes.** Internal app and robot OS share the same version string. External app uses calendar semver; external buildroot uses an independent traditional semver line (for example `v1.19.9`).

Calendar components use **US Eastern** (`America/New_York`):

- **Major (YY):** two-digit year (2026 → `26`; breaks after 2099)
- **Minor (M):** month without leading zeros (June → `6`)

**Internal (`internal@`):** patch is `DNN = day * 100 + build_num` (build 1–99 per day). Same-day bumps increment DNN. Alpha/beta use bare `-alpha` / `-beta` suffixes.

Examples (May 26, 2026):

- `internal@26.5.2601` (first stable internal)
- `internal@26.5.2601-alpha` (first alpha internal)
- `internal@26.5.2602-alpha` (second alpha internal same day)

**External app (`v` on opentrons-ot2):** patch **N** is monthly build counter **0–9** (first release in June 2026 → `v26.6.0`). Each external release in the month (stable, alpha, or beta) takes the next **N** slot. More than 10 external releases per month is a process failure.

External app alpha/beta use semver prerelease numbering on that build's base: `v26.5.1-alpha.0`, `v26.5.1-alpha.1`, `v26.5.1-beta.0`. After `v26.5.0` stable, the next build is `v26.5.1-alpha.0`, not `v26.5.0-alpha.0`.

**External robot OS (`v` on buildroot):** independent traditional semver line (for example `v1.19.9`). `go` patch-bumps from the latest merged traditional tag; it does not mirror the app calendar version.

External tags use a `v` prefix; internal tags use `internal@`.

### Flex internal vs external branching

| Path / channel | Default branch to tag | Version inference (default) |
|---|---|---|
| **Flex internal** | Default branch HEAD (`opentrons`: `edge`, `oe-core` / `ot3-firmware`: `main`) | Highest `ot3@X.Y.Z` base from app repo tag catalog |
| **Flex external** | `chore_release-<version>` when present on remote, else default branch | Highest `chore_release-X.Y.Z` on `opentrons`, fallback latest `v*` tag base |
| **OT-2 internal / external** | Default branch HEAD (`opentrons-ot2`: `edge`, `buildroot`: `opentrons-develop`) | Calendar semver for app + internal (`YY.M.DNN` internal, `YY.M.N` external app); buildroot external patch bump from latest traditional `v*` tag |

**Branch overrides:** `--app-branch <branch>` on the app monorepo; `--stack-branch oe-core=main` (repeatable) per stack repo. Example: internal beta from `edge` on `opentrons` with `main` on oe-core and firmware.

Internal tags: coordinated `ot3@` / `v*` on `opentrons` and `oe-core`. `ot3-firmware` uses the same `ot3@*` internally; external stack `v*` maps to `ex*` on firmware plus integer `vN` on the same commit. OT-2 app and buildroot share `internal@` calendar tags. OT-2 external app uses calendar `vYY.M.N`; buildroot external uses independent traditional `vX.Y.Z`.

### Flex semver tagging

Flex uses **coordinated stack tags** on `opentrons` and `oe-core`. In `just go`, Flex prompts for **Stability: stable/alpha/beta** (legacy `unstable` maps to `alpha`).

| Repo | Internal | External |
|---|---|---|
| `opentrons` (app) | `ot3@X.Y.Z`, alpha `ot3@X.Y.Z-alpha.N`, beta `ot3@X.Y.Z-beta.N` | `vX.Y.Z`, alpha `vX.Y.Z-alpha.N`, beta `vX.Y.Z-beta.N` |
| `oe-core` (robot OS) | same stack tag as app | same stack tag as app |
| `ot3-firmware` | same `ot3@*` as app + integer `vN` | `exX.Y.Z…` (from stack `v*`) + integer `vN` |

Tag suggestion rules in `automation/go.py`:

- **App (`opentrons` / `opentrons-ot2`):** base `X.Y.Z` (Flex) or calendar version (OT-2) from the prompted release version. Flex stable: `ot3@X.Y.Z` / `vX.Y.Z` if missing, else patch bump. Flex alpha/beta: **independent lane counters** at the same base (for example `ot3@4.0.0-alpha.3` and `ot3@4.0.0-beta.0` can coexist). Next tag numbers are read from the **app monorepo tag catalog** (`opentrons` for Flex, `opentrons-ot2` for OT-2). Change logs compare against the prior tag in the **same stability lane** merged into the release branch.
- **Robot OS (`oe-core`):** same stack tag as the app. Retag unchanged commits when the repo did not change.
- **Firmware (`ot3-firmware`):** coordination tag is `ot3@*` (internal) or `ex*` mapped from stack `v*` (external). Integer `vN` is globally unique in the firmware repo; suggest a new `vN` only when the release commit does not already have one. Retag-only releases need only the coordination tag.
- **Before pushing the app tag:** run `just validate-release-tags --tag <app-tag>`. `oe-core` `build-refs` maps external stack tags to `ex*` on firmware ([PR #329](https://github.com/Opentrons/oe-core/pull/329)); missing tags fail (no `:latest:` fallback).

**Flex release flavors** (same `X.Y.Z` base, independent lanes; not a strict promote-alpha-to-beta ladder):

| Lane | Stability in `go` | Tag example | Typical use |
|---|---|---|---|
| VM isolation | `beta` | `ot3@4.0.0-beta.0` | Beta app channel |
| CRS | `alpha` | `ot3@4.0.0-alpha.4` | Alpha app channel; can ship after beta on the same base |

When **both** beta and alpha channels need fresh builds in the **same cycle**, ship beta before alpha so beta desktop builds do not leave `alpha.yml` pointing at the wrong build. That updater YAML rule does **not** require alpha to precede beta on the semver base.

### OT-2 semver tagging

| Repo | Internal | External |
|---|---|---|
| `opentrons-ot2` (app) | `internal@YY.M.DNN`, alpha/beta bare suffix | `vYY.M.N`, alpha/beta `-alpha.N` / `-beta.N` (next monthly build slot) |
| `buildroot` (robot OS) | same calendar version as app | independent `vX.Y.Z` line; patch bump from latest merged traditional tag |

Tag suggestion rules in `automation/go.py`:

- **App (`opentrons-ot2`):** calendar semver from synced app tags. Stable external: next monthly **N** (counts all external builds in the month). Alpha/beta external: next **N** for a new build line, or increment prerelease on the current alpha/beta base. Internal: same-day build counter in patch.
- **Robot OS (`buildroot`, internal):** same calendar allocation as the app.
- **Robot OS (`buildroot`, external):** patch bump from the latest merged traditional `v*` tag (for example `v1.19.9` → `v1.19.10`). Ignores calendar app tags like `v26.5.0`.

### Tag push order

Push annotated tags in this order. Dependent stack repos first, app monorepo last.

| Path | Order |
|---|---|
| **Flex** | 1. `ot3-firmware` (if needed), 2. `oe-core` (if needed), 3. `opentrons` (app, always last) |
| **OT-2** | 1. `buildroot` (if needed), 2. `opentrons-ot2` (app, always last) |

`go` prints this order at the end of a release run.

### Track release builds (`just track-builds`)

After pushing the **app** tag, run `just track-builds --path flex|ot2 --tag <app-tag> --wait` (or without `--wait` for a one-shot lookup). `go` prints this command with `--wait` by default.

`automation/track_builds.py` locates GitHub Actions runs for:

1. **App** workflow on the monorepo (`App test, build, and deploy`)
2. **Kickoff** cross-repo dispatch (`Start OT-2 build` or `Start Flex build`)
3. **Robot OS** build in `buildroot` (OT-2) or `oe-core` (Flex)

The Rich table also lists matching **key jobs** (deploy, desktop builds, dispatch spawn, robot image build). The **Slack copy block** includes only two links:

```
OT-2 release `internal@26.5.2801`

- app: https://github.com/Opentrons/opentrons-ot2/actions/runs/...
- ot2: https://github.com/Opentrons/buildroot/actions/runs/...
```

(Flex uses `- flex:` instead of `- ot2:`.)

**`--wait` behavior:** poll every 15 seconds (default) until App, Kickoff, and Robot OS workflow runs all appear, up to 900 seconds (default). The poll loop only checks for workflow runs (not jobs). After all three runs exist, the script fetches key jobs with retries for transient GitHub 404s on the jobs API. Exit code `2` if any top-level run is still missing.

Tag prefix inference when `--path` is omitted: `internal@` → OT-2, `ot3@` → Flex, otherwise Flex.

### CloudFront invalidation (`just invalidate-cloudfront`)

After builds finish, run `just invalidate-cloudfront --path flex|ot2 --tag <app-tag>` to print a copy-paste `aws cloudfront create-invalidation` command (it does not run invalidation). Uses `--profile robotics_robot_stack_prod-admin`. Hosts come from `robot-stack-infra` prod domains:

| Path | Channel | Host | Infra stack |
|---|---|---|---|
| Flex | external | `builds.opentrons.com` | `release-ci` |
| Flex | internal | `ot3-development.builds.opentrons.com` | `ot3-ci` |
| OT-2 | external | `ot2.builds.opentrons.com` | `ot2-ci` |
| OT-2 | internal | `ot2-development.builds.opentrons.com` | `ot2-internal-ci` |

Invalidation paths are `/app/*` plus `/ot3-oe/*` (Flex) or `/ot2-br/*` (OT-2). When AWS credentials are available, the distribution ID is resolved automatically; otherwise a lookup command and placeholder are shown.

## Tooling safety model

These scripts are **advisory**. They gather state, print tables, copy blocks, and suggested shell commands. A human (or agent) runs the printed commands manually.

| Action | Who performs it |
|---|---|
| `git clone`, `git fetch`, `git pull`, `git tag -l`, `git log` (local repo sync/read) | `just go` only |
| `git tag -a`, `git push`, workflow dispatch, CloudFront invalidation, S3 uploads | **Not automated**; printed as copy-paste commands |
| Read GitHub Actions / AWS CloudFront distribution IDs | `track-builds`, `invalidate-cloudfront` (lookup only) |
| Fetch public S3/CloudFront manifests over HTTPS | asset inventory scripts |
| Write local HTML under `.build/` or `pages/` | `ot2-assets`, `flex-assets`, `assets-pages` |

Nothing in this repo creates release tags, pushes tags, triggers CI, invalidates CloudFront, or publishes artifacts unless an operator runs the printed commands elsewhere.

## Agentic CLI reference

All release tools accept CLI flags so agents can run them without prompts. Use `--non-interactive` where documented to fail fast instead of blocking on stdin.

Run everything via `uv run just <recipe> ...` or `uv run ./automation/<script>.py ...`.

### Typical release sequence

1. **Plan tags:** `just go --non-interactive --skip-assumptions --path flex|ot2 --release-type internal|external --stability ... [--version ...]`
2. **Human:** run printed tag commands in each repo (stack repos first, app last). Check out the release branch in each repo when `go` prints `git checkout …`
3. **Validate coordinated tags (Flex):** `just validate-release-tags --tag <app-tag>` before pushing the app tag
4. **Track CI:** `just track-builds --non-interactive --path flex|ot2 --tag <app-tag> --wait`
5. **Human:** wait for builds; validate manifests if needed (`just ot2-assets` / `just flex-assets`)
6. **Print invalidation:** `just invalidate-cloudfront --non-interactive --path flex|ot2 --tag <app-tag>`
7. **Human:** run the printed `aws cloudfront create-invalidation` command

### `just go` (`automation/go.py`)

Syncs stack repos locally and prints release analysis plus suggested tag commands.

**Side effects:** clone/fetch/pull in workspace repo directories (`opentrons/`, `oe-core/`, etc.).

| Flag | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `--path flex\|ot2` | Robot path (default: `flex`, or prompt) |
| `--release-type internal\|external` | Channel (default: `external`, or prompt) |
| `--stability` | OT-2: `stable`, `alpha`, `beta`. Flex: `stable`, `alpha`, `beta` (legacy `unstable` → `alpha`) |
| `--version` | Base version. Flex: `vX.Y.Z`. OT-2 internal: `YY.M.DNN`. OT-2 external: `YY.M.N` |
| `--app-branch` | Branch to tag in the app monorepo (`opentrons` or `opentrons-ot2`) |
| `--stack-branch REPO=BRANCH` | Branch to tag for a stack repo (repeatable; e.g. `oe-core=main`) |
| `--skip-assumptions` | Omit the assumptions panel (cleaner agent output) |
| `--non-interactive` | Never prompt; use defaults for omitted flags |

**Defaults with `--non-interactive`:** path `flex`, release `external`, stability `stable`. Flex external version is inferred from the highest `chore_release-X.Y.Z` branch on `opentrons` (fallback: latest `v*` tag base). Flex internal version is inferred from the highest `ot3@X.Y.Z` base in the app repo tag catalog.

**Examples:**

```bash
just go --non-interactive --skip-assumptions --path ot2 --release-type internal --stability alpha
just go --non-interactive --skip-assumptions --path flex --release-type internal --stability beta --version v4.0.0
just go --non-interactive --skip-assumptions --path flex --release-type internal --stability alpha --version v4.0.0 --app-branch edge --stack-branch oe-core=main --stack-branch ot3-firmware=main
```

**Output includes:** latest-tag summary (stable / alpha / beta lanes at the semver base), release flavor lanes panel, change-since-tag tables (same lane on release branch), tag push order, per-repo tag plans (`git checkout` when release branch differs from default, then `git tag -a` / `git push` suggestions), app tag section, and a **Next steps** panel with `track-builds` and `invalidate-cloudfront` commands.

### `just track-builds` (`automation/track_builds.py`)

Locates GitHub Actions runs for app, kickoff, and robot OS workflows. Prints Rich tables, key jobs, and a Slack copy block (`app` + `ot2`/`flex` links only).

**Side effects:** read-only (`gh` API). No git or AWS writes.

| Flag | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `--path flex\|ot2` | Robot path (default: infer from tag prefix, else `flex`) |
| `--tag` | App release tag (required with `--non-interactive`) |
| `--release-type internal\|external` | Prefix bare tags like `26.5.2601` or `8.5.0` |
| `--wait` | Poll until app, kickoff, and robot OS runs appear |
| `--wait-timeout` | Max wait seconds (default `900`) |
| `--poll-seconds` | Poll interval (default `15`) |
| `--run-limit` | Monorepo runs to scan (default `40`) |
| `--robot-max-pages` | Robot OS repo run pages (default `5`) |
| `--non-interactive` | Require `--tag`; no prompts |

**Exit codes:** `1` on runtime error; `2` if top-level workflow runs still missing after lookup/wait.

```bash
just track-builds --non-interactive --path ot2 --tag internal@26.5.2601 --wait
```

### `just invalidate-cloudfront` (`automation/invalidate_cloudfront.py`)

Prints CloudFront host mapping, distribution ID (when AWS creds allow lookup), paths, and a copy-paste `aws cloudfront create-invalidation` command. **Does not run invalidation.**

| Flag | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `--path flex\|ot2` | Robot path (default: infer from tag) |
| `--tag` | App release tag (required with `--non-interactive`) |
| `--release-type internal\|external` | Prefix bare tags |
| `--aws-profile` | AWS profile for lookup (default: `robotics_robot_stack_prod-admin`) |
| `--skip-cloudfront-lookup` | Skip AWS lookup; print placeholder distribution ID |
| `--non-interactive` | Require `--tag`; no prompts |

```bash
just invalidate-cloudfront --non-interactive --path flex --tag ot3@8.5.0-alpha.1
just invalidate-cloudfront --non-interactive --path ot2 --tag internal@26.5.2601 --skip-cloudfront-lookup
```

### `just validate-release-tags` (`automation/validate_release_tags.py`)

Verifies coordinated Flex release tags locally. Checks stack tags on `opentrons` and `oe-core`, the mapped coordination tag on `ot3-firmware` (`ex*` for external stack `v*`, same `ot3@*` for internal), and an integer `vN` version tag on the same firmware commit. Read-only unless `--fetch` (runs `git fetch --tags` in each clone).

| Flag | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `--tag` | Stack release tag (required; e.g. `ot3@8.5.0-beta.0`, `v10.0.0-alpha.0`) |
| `--fetch` | Fetch tags from origin before checking |

**Exit codes:** `0` if all checks pass; `1` if any missing or fetch fails.

```bash
just validate-release-tags --tag ot3@8.5.0-beta.1
just validate-release-tags --fetch --tag v10.0.0-alpha.0
```

### Asset inventory (`just ot2-assets`, `just flex-assets`, `just assets-pages`)

Fetch live S3/CloudFront manifests and write HTML reports. Read-only against public URLs except local file writes.

| Recipe | Script | Default output |
|---|---|---|
| `just ot2-assets` | `automation/ot2_assets.py` | `.build/ot2-assets.html` |
| `just flex-assets` | `automation/flex_assets.py` | `.build/flex-assets.html` |
| `just assets-pages` | `automation/publish_assets_pages.py` | `pages/` (index + per-channel asset inventories + release guides) |
| `just assets-serve` | same with `--serve --open-browser` | serves `pages/` on port `8765` |

Shared flags (per-platform scripts): `--limit`, `--output`, `--serve`, `--port`, `--open-browser`.

`assets-pages` flags: `--output-dir`, `--limit`, `--serve`, `--port`, `--open-browser`.

